spanGrp.span: damo phunchung pām hang hrowng tinu̠ punchung pām
this, went up to Phunchung village, Phunchung village.
? dahtung dahtung mite hli vehnu̠ bu̠ phu̠wnnu̠ dah lu dah lu vaṭow vamo ame
How people cultivate fields, plant rice, do all kinds of things?
I really want to ask you.
May ṭha thung vana phu̠wn hin e
What they planted in the month of May
And a very strong wind was blowing.
amatuwng vachọ vabāl hinhe mahe ṭha pāmi
As a result, their plnts and crops are not good.
tuvarende vahli ve hin e khang nunge nungeka
But the fields they cultivate are very nice.
On every hill they cultivate these fields.
They built field-huts very nicely, like that.
atunghe majalki kara to ahrọjenu̠ hangkal ṭhu̠ jenu̠
Now they plucked cucumbers etc. and climed with it up (to the outposts).
So nice, as I went there.
asinki hlāng ṭum kheh ahangle lening no diinu̠
I will come back one more time
charahin hli ve to so ṭum kheh hangma le vaning
I did not go back a single time to the fields that my children cultivate.
atatuwng amato pām tobe āhrowlval ne
You went all around that place, right?
hang hrowng tinu̠ ama pām lue
you went far away, that kind of village
dahtung dahtung pām e be ingnu̠ mo
I really want to ask you.
anihin sake thungki, Vango hli hnih e
The fields belonging to Vango, from our clan
rowlsaki kahang thungki kana vehrang e atung kumso ṭu̠naka vadọ mangje

When I went there before, they say that it is the time of what they were supposed to cultivate (i.e. the time to cultivate the discussed plot, after the needed years of recovery in slash-and-burn cultivation).
kum sowm chahe ṭu̠naka vadọmang amato
They say it will be ten years (i.e. a full cultivation cycle for the given plot).
iṭha pāva ama pām e so amato
eh anihin sake ki hli e
amato so- vāsowm nato nituwng veenu̠
eh bu̠ e tin chama kakun jā khu̠va
It wasn't a really bad year.
atung kum te ṭu̠naka dọnu̠ aku̠w veenaka mo?
Now, this year, who is going to cultivate?
anite napāngkal ammanu̠, ihang le pachāng ma sinnu̠
I have no strength, I cannot go back.
moshum hin veeje naka mo mochu̠l vēje naka mo atatuwng amato so
It will be cultivated either by Moshums or by Mochuls, like that
Wangote hli hnih e khang hnim hnimnu̠ atungso
mi'ing sake lue vee chanā jā naka
nangte ichọọ jumjum va tinu̠ sungṭha pāmha
Since you go all around restlessly, to Sungtha village
hnuwnghring hli vee khe isu chọọ tinu̠
you also went to see the fields cultivated by HnHr (your daughter).
amakite sungṭha hli ve dahchā dahchā i ing vamo
so how are the fields cultivated by Sungtha (people)?
Last year they slashed Malebang hill.
vahli hangchọọ lalanu̠ peerih khe pariinu̠
I used to go there often, and also stayed overnight.
but it was a bad year.
They also did not take a lot of rice.
damo joso vahli hnih hin joso ruwngchin nimanu̠
Also the field are not beautiful.
The place that they are going this year
ama hato hangje(nu̠) khang sow isova
it is almost stretching up to there.
I followed them to that place.
amato pām e to khang nunge nunge ka minamso chuinka
That is a very nice place, the ash gourd is bearing fruit, too.
pasu̠'ng te vabu̠ hinto khang du̠ vadu̠mang turende
Rats ate their rice a lot.
minam ki kara majal ki kara
are all very good, in their place
asān nanu̠ napahin hring thung pirāl pām naamthung
Formerly, when our parents were alive, when we lived in Pirāl
mi'ing hli vana veete napu̠ kodilpa ?? napahin hring thung ki mi'ng hli va naveete [neveete]
What people cultivate, in the time Kodil's father and our parents were alive, what people cultivate
nunge tangna mi- hliva mi hlivapha vika
So nice, peop- field cultivation, the cultivation time is approaching.
dọnu̠ mi hli vā he mi avang thuwnu̠
ara- avang thuwnu̠ napu̠ kodilpa to owng ruruh nu̠
They came out, our grandfather Kodil-pa (Kodil's father) was shouting.
"Let's go and take a look at the placeǃ"
hli su chọọhin chaka ve dọnu̠
Let's go look at the field, he said.
as he said, our father, from the bottom of the village
time after time, they cultivated it early.
Even burning, they did it early.
peethun cha hrangto aval luto amnu̠
there were old people who would start the cultivation.
bu̠ phu̠wn phatuwng joso aval lutuwng atatuwng "Bu̠ phu̠wn pha vika"
Also in the time of planting rice, old people (would let know) "The rice planting time is approachingǃ".
The time of cleaning up and burning (the hillside fields) is comingǃ
what is said, the old people did everything, and then
chahli bal ivē pha vika, bu̠ phu̠wn pha vika idọhe aval vathi tiiva
The rice fields, old people know it all, that the cultivation time is near, that the rice planting time is near.
